Class FractionallyUnbalancedWhenNoExpectations

    OverExpectedCriterion

    public class FractionallyUnbalancedWhenNoExpectations
extends FractionallyOverExpected
    Avoid unbalanced sections when there are no expectations. When there are expectations, the FractionallyOverExpected is used. If there are no expectations, sections that would have more students than given by the balance are marked as over-expected. The target fill ratio is proportional to the section size, a section is considered unbalanced, when the target fill is exceeded by more than OverExpected.Disbalance percentage (defaults to 0.1). Unlimited sections are also balanced, when General.BalanceUnlimited parameter is set to true (defaults to false).

    A class of an offering with no expectations is over-expected when the number of enrolled students (including the student in question) minus the target fill is over the OverExpected.Disbalance portion of the section limit.
